This sim serves 2 purposes:
1. It tests the functionality of the EphemBasedPointingRefFrame class.  This
   class is a very simple inheritance from PointingRefFrame.  Testing of the
   PointingRefFrame is conducted in SIM_verif; this test is limited to the very
   small difference between the two classes.
2. It illustrates the potential pitfalls of using a PointingRefFrame
   instance rather than an EphemPointingRefFrame instance when the
   reference-frames are managed by the Ephemerides Manager.  See RUN_13 and
   RUN_14 for easy mistakes to avoid.
